{{Infobox University |name = USC School of Dramatic Arts |established = 1945 |type = [[Private university|Private]] [[drama school]] |dean = David Bridel |city = [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]] |state = [[California]] |country = United States |website = http://dramaticarts.usc.edu/ }}
The '''USC School of Dramatic Arts (SDA)''' (formerly the '''USC School of Theatre''') is the dramatic arts school at the [[University of Southern California]]. It is ranked one of the top 10 dramatic arts schools in the world, according to The Hollywood Reporter's Top 25 Drama Schools.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/top-25-undergraduate-drama-schools-895399/item/ucla-top-25-undergraduate-drama-895418 |title=The Top 25 Undergraduate Drama Schools Ranked |publisher=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=2016-05-20}}</ref> The USC School of Dramatic Arts offers Bachelor of Arts degrees in theatre and visual & performing arts; Bachelor of Fine Arts degrees in acting, design, sound design, stage management and technical direction; and Master of Fine Arts degrees in acting and dramatic writing.
==History== Founded in 1945 as ''Department of Drama at USC'', it became an independent school in 1991 and was named ''USC School of Theatre''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rfpdb.com/process/download/name/SCHOOL-BRANDING-&-WEB-SERVICES.pdf |format=PDF |title=USC SChool of Theatre Branding & Web Services |date=2010 |page=22 |accessdate=2012-11-05}}</ref> It was renamed USC School of Dramatic Arts on July 1, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.usc.edu/#!/article/33558/theatre-school-renamed-usc-school-of-dramatic-arts/ |title=Theatre school renamed USC School of Dramatic Arts |date=2012-04-23 |publisher=USC News, University of Southern California |accessdate=2012-11-05}}</ref>
